00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:58.840
I think that's a really interesting point.

00:05:58.840 --> 00:06:04.960
And there have been a lot of languages that are easy to read, like VB is a language you could read pretty easy, right?

00:06:04.960 --> 00:06:05.420
Visual Basic.

00:06:05.420 --> 00:06:10.800
But a lot of the ones that are easy to start with have these pretty low ceilings.

00:06:10.800 --> 00:06:14.000
It's like, well, you can build up to this point, but you want to build something real.

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:17.380
You put that away and you get out the Java, you get out the C++.

00:06:17.380 --> 00:06:21.200
And Python doesn't have really that ceiling quite nearly as low.

00:06:21.200 --> 00:06:24.540
And I think that's partly one of the things that makes it really special.

00:06:24.540 --> 00:06:24.920
Yeah.

00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:27.140
And that's been one of the huge elements for me.

00:06:27.140 --> 00:06:31.560
I mean, I've been doing Python daily for several years now going through.

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:35.820
And I still go back to some of the fundamental skills that I learned in those early classes.

00:06:35.820 --> 00:06:40.340
But the programs I'm building are much more sophisticated than some of the early ones that go through.

00:06:40.340 --> 00:06:46.140
And when I look at some of the new features that come into the language, they're really exciting things that are coming after it.

00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:49.320
But they're being put in a way that you don't have to use those, right?

00:06:49.340 --> 00:06:55.440
It still gives you this ability to kind of work your way into Python, absorb the capabilities when it makes sense for you.

00:06:55.440 --> 00:06:56.360
And there's a challenge there.

00:06:56.360 --> 00:06:57.860
It's not like with JavaScript.

00:06:57.860 --> 00:07:05.720
It feels like you have to like immediately you're embedded inside of all sorts of promise statements and multiple levels of like embedded.

00:07:05.720 --> 00:07:07.440
And you can't do anything.

00:07:07.440 --> 00:07:09.640
With Python, you can start really simple.

00:07:10.040 --> 00:07:17.620
And then when the time calls for it, there's all of this other stuff that you can pull out and become very sophisticated as far as the language goes.

00:07:17.620 --> 00:07:17.940
Yeah.

00:07:17.940 --> 00:07:22.120
That's part of its sort of elasticity up and down the experience scale, right?

00:07:22.120 --> 00:07:26.520
You don't have, like you said, you don't have to be an expert in all of Python to build interesting things.

00:07:26.520 --> 00:07:32.080
Like you maybe don't even know what a function is, but you could still do some pretty interesting stuff in straight down.

00:07:32.080 --> 00:07:35.820
You know, you don't need to care about code reused or whatever, right?

00:07:35.820 --> 00:07:36.100
Yep.

00:07:36.100 --> 00:07:39.780
It's object oriented under the hood, but you can completely ignore objects.

00:07:39.780 --> 00:07:42.140
Until you realize that there's value in it.

00:07:42.140 --> 00:07:45.500
And hell, half my code still ignores objects, it seems like these days.

00:07:45.500 --> 00:07:47.060
Yeah, that's quite an interesting point.

